## Long Operation Completion SMS (MANDATORY)

**RULE**: When completing any operation that took more than 10 minutes, send an SMS notification.

```powershell
Send-Sms $smsNumber "WindowsDb2Editor: [TASK] completed successfully. [DETAILS]"
```

**When to send:**
- After completing long refactoring operations (> 10 min)
- After completing full test suite runs (> 10 min)
- After completing database-wide operations (> 10 min)

**Message Format:**
```
WindowsDb2Editor: [TaskName] complete. Build: [PASSED/FAILED]. Tests: [X/Y passed]. Duration: [Xm].
```

## Hourly Status SMS (During Continuous Implementation)

**RULE**: During continuous implementation, send hourly SMS updates.

```powershell
Send-Sms "+4797188358" "WindowsDb2Editor: [TIME] Progress [X]% - [Y] tasks done, [Z] remaining. Current: [task]"
```

## Stop Protocol (CRITICAL)

**If battery < 10% OR continuous implementation must be stopped:**

1. **Commit all changes**: Ensure all code is committed to git
2. **Sync with remote**: Push changes to remote repository
3. **Send SMS notification**:
   ```powershell
   Send-Sms "+4797188358" "WindowsDb2Editor: Implementation stopped at [X]% - All changes committed & pushed"
   ```
